('77f4db2e-9d3b-47aa-8d56-71e84129b300', 'progress', 'signed', '{"subjective":"Patient reports substernal chest pressure began 2 hours prior to arrival. Radiating to left arm. Associated diaphoresis and nausea. Pain 8/10 at presentation, now 2/10 post-intervention.","objective":"ECG: ST elevation V1-V4 with reciprocal changes in II, III, aVF. Troponin I: 12.4 ng/mL (↑). Echo: EF 35%, anterior wall akinesis. Cath: 100% occlusion of LAD, successful PCI with DES placement. TIMI 3 flow restored. Door-to-balloon: 62 minutes.","assessment":"Acute anterior STEMI with successful primary PCI to LAD. Reduced EF 35% with regional wall motion abnormality. Cardiogenic shock not present.","plan":"1. DAPT: Aspirin 81mg + Ticagrelor 90mg BID\n2. Heparin gtt per ACS protocol\n3. Metoprolol 12.5mg PO BID (hold if HR <55 or SBP <100)\n4. Atorvastatin 80mg daily\n5. Serial troponins q6h\n6. Repeat echo in 48-72h\n7. Cardiac rehab referral"}', now() - interval '1 day'),
('77f4db2e-9d3b-47aa-8d56-71e84129b300', 'progress', 'draft', '{"subjective":"No recurrent chest pain. Mild fatigue. Tolerated ambulation to bathroom with assistance. No orthopnea or PND.","objective":"HR 72 (NSR), BP 118/72, RR 16, SpO2 98% RA. Troponin trending: 12.4 → 8.2 → 4.1 (down-trending). No new ST changes. Lungs clear. JVP not elevated. Groin access site: clean, no hematoma. Pedal pulses 2+ bilaterally.","assessment":"STEMI day 2. Hemodynamically stable post-PCI. Troponins down-trending as expected. No signs of heart failure.","plan":"1. Continue DAPT and statin\n2. Start ACE inhibitor (Lisinopril 2.5mg) today\n3. Advance activity as tolerated\n4. Echocardiogram repeat tomorrow\n5. HbA1c and lipid panel if not done\n6. Smoking cessation counseling\n7. Anticipated transfer to step-down unit today"}', now());

