('90cbf7e5-5a35-4221-8e57-d932017ab4bf', 'progress', 'signed', '{"subjective":"MEDITECH SURGICAL NOTE — POD 2 from laparoscopic right hemicolectomy for cecal mass. Patient reports mild incisional pain (3/10). No nausea. Has passed flatus. No bowel movement yet.","objective":"T 37.4°C, HR 76, BP 128/78. Abdomen: soft, mildly tender at port sites, no distension. Incisions clean and dry. Bowel sounds present in all quadrants. JP drain: minimal serous output. Diet: tolerating clear liquids.","assessment":"Post-op day 2 from laparoscopic right hemicolectomy. Return of bowel function (flatus). Recovering well. Pathology pending.","plan":"1. Advance diet to regular as tolerated\n2. Increase ambulation — goal 4 laps/day\n3. Continue PCA → transition to PO pain meds today\n4. Remove JP drain if output continues low\n5. Path results expected tomorrow\n6. DVT prophylaxis until ambulatory\n7. Target discharge POD 3-4"}', now() - interval '6 hours');

