('029266f0-acc4-45df-96b3-a47bc96fdf6e', 'progress', 'signed', '{"subjective":"MEDITECH SURGICAL NOTE — 67M with history of prior abdominal surgeries presenting with 2 days of crampy abdominal pain, nausea, vomiting, and obstipation. Last BM 3 days ago.","objective":"T 37.6°C, HR 98, BP 136/84. Abdomen: distended, diffusely tender without peritoneal signs. High-pitched tinkling bowel sounds. CT abdomen: small bowel obstruction with transition point in right lower quadrant, likely adhesive. No pneumatosis or free air. Lactate 1.2.","assessment":"Adhesive small bowel obstruction, partial. No signs of strangulation or ischemia currently.","plan":"1. NGT decompression — 800mL bilious output on placement\n2. NPO, IV fluids NS at 125mL/hr\n3. Serial abdominal exams q4h\n4. Gastrografin challenge tomorrow if no improvement\n5. If peritoneal signs or clinical decline → OR for lysis of adhesions\n6. DVT prophylaxis\n7. Nutrition consult if NPO >5 days"}', now() - interval '1 day'),
('029266f0-acc4-45df-96b3-a47bc96fdf6e', 'progress', 'draft', '{"subjective":"Mild improvement in pain. NGT output decreasing. No vomiting since NGT placed.","objective":"NGT output: 300mL/8h shift (↓). Abdomen less distended. Mild tenderness. No peritoneal signs. KUB: still dilated loops but improved air-fluid levels. Lactate 0.9.","assessment":"SBO with early signs of resolution. Conservative management appropriate. No surgical indicators at this time.","plan":"1. Gastrografin 100mL via NGT today\n2. Follow-up KUB in 6 hours\n3. If contrast reaches colon, clamp NGT and trial clear liquids\n4. Continue serial abdominal exams\n5. If no resolution by day 3, surgical intervention"}', now());

