('a1ba7991-4565-47a9-a884-705e81de436f', 'progress', 'signed', '{"subjective":"MEDITECH LTC NOTE — 82F with advanced dementia (GDS 6), CHF, and CKD stage 3b. Caregiver reports patient more confused than baseline over past 2 days. Decreased oral intake. No fever, cough, or urinary symptoms.","objective":"T 37.0°C, HR 78, BP 108/62, SpO2 95% on RA. Weight 52kg (↓1kg from last month). Alert but disoriented to time and place. No focal neuro deficits beyond baseline. UA: trace leukocytes, negative nitrite. BMP: Na 132, K 4.2, Cr 1.6 (baseline 1.4), BUN 38.","assessment":"Acute-on-chronic cognitive decline. Differential: dehydration, UTI, medication effect, disease progression. Mild AKI likely pre-renal.","plan":"1. PO fluid challenge: 500mL over 4 hours\n2. Repeat BMP tomorrow\n3. Monitor I/O closely\n4. Medication review — hold metformin (Cr elevated)\n5. If worsening confusion, urine culture and CXR\n6. Palliative care team aware — comfort-focused care plan\n7. Family updated on status"}', now() - interval '1 day');

